text: Trade is expected to dominate talks between the Prime Minister and his Indonesian counterpart, Joko Widodo when the pair meet in Jakarta. Scott Morrison will attend the inauguration of the Indonesian President for his second term of power. Talks at the presidential palace are expected to focus on the 16-nation Regional Comprehensive Economic Partnership, which is hoped to be struck by the end of the year. Other leaders attending the Indonesian President's inauguration include the Malaysian Prime Minister, Singapore Prime Minister and the Sultan of Brunei.
